    {"repo": "chromium/chromium", "path": "content/browser/browser_main_loop.cc", "symbol": "BrowserMainLoop"},
    {"repo": "chromium/chromium", "path": "content/renderer/render_thread_impl.cc", "symbol": "RenderThreadImpl"},
    {"repo": "chromium/chromium", "path": "content/browser/child_process_launcher.cc", "symbol": "ChildProcessLauncher"},
    {"repo": "chromium/chromium", "path": "content/common/renderer.mojom", "symbol": "content.mojom.Renderer"}
  ],
  "text": "Chromium's multi-process architecture is centered around five key components located in the chromium/chromium repository:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.cc) - This class represents the browser-side connection to a renderer process. It manages the lifecycle, IPC communication, and resource allocation for each renderer process. There is one RenderProcessHost instance per renderer process.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.cc) - This class manages the main browser process event loop. It initializes critical browser subsystems including the UI thread, I/O thread, and various message loops. The constructor takes MainFunctionParams and handles initialization of mojo bindings, message pumps, and other critical browser infrastructure.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.cc) - This class represents the main thread of a renderer process. It manages the renderer's message loop, handles incoming IPC messages from the browser, and coordinates renderer-side initialization including graphics, input, and plugin management.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.cc) - This component is responsible for spawning and managing child processes (renderers, utilities, plugins, etc.) in a platform-independent way. It handles process creation, sandboxing setup, and platform-specific launch mechanisms with helper implementations for Linux, macOS, Windows, and iOS.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer Interface** (content/common/renderer.mojom) - This Mojo interface definition declares the IPC contract for browser-to-renderer communication. It defines the messages and data structures exchanged between the browser process and renderer processes using Chromium's Mojo IPC system.\n\nThese five components form the backbone of Chromium's multi-process architecture, enabling secure process isolation while maintaining efficient inter-process communication between the browser and multiple renderer processes."
}

